#1.5 A
max_accuracy={}
max_recall={}
score=[]
methods=['manhattan','euclidean','cosine','jaccard','minkowski','hamming']
for i in range(1,20):
    for j in methods:
        kn=KNN(i,metric=j)
        kn.fit(np.array(X_train),np.ravel(y_train))
        y_pred=kn.predict(np.array(X_test))
        max_accuracy[str(i)+'_'+str(j)]=accuracy_score(np.array(y_test),np.array(y_pred))
        score.append(accuracy_score(np.array(y_test),np.array(y_pred)))
        max_recall[str(i)+'_'+str(j)]=recall_score(y_test,y_pred,average='micro')
In [230]:
max(max_accuracy,key=max_accuracy.get)

score=[]

for i in range(1,20):
        kn=KNN(i,metric='manhattan')
        kn.fit(np.array(X_train),np.ravel(y_train))
        y_pred=kn.predict(np.array(X_test))
        score.append(accuracy_score(np.array(y_test),np.array(y_pred)))
plt.plot(range(1,20),score,color = 'blue',linestyle='dashed', 
         marker='o',markerfacecolor='red', markersize=10)
plt.title('accuracy vs. K Value')
plt.xlabel('K')

#2.4 B
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier 

max_accuracy={}
max_recall={}
score=[]
methods=['manhattan','euclidean','cosine','jaccard','minkowski','hamming']
for i in range(1,20):
    for j in methods:
        kn=KNeighborsClassifier(i,metric=j)
        kn.fit(np.array(xtrain1),np.ravel(ytrain1))
        y_pred=kn.predict(np.array(xtest1))
        max_accuracy[str(i)+'_'+str(j)]=accuracy_score(np.array(ytest1.astype(int)),np.array(y_pred))
        score.append(accuracy_score(np.array(ytest1),np.array(y_pred)))
        max_recall[str(i)+'_'+str(j)]=recall_score(ytest1,y_pred,average='micro')
